Interface ICmd2ModelAdapter

      <T extends IRoomConnectionData> void sendMessageToRoom(T data)
      Send a message to the chatroom without datapackets. The local machine should wrap this data into a DataPacket and send it to every dyad in the chatroom.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of the message being sent. Bounded by IRoomConnectionData since this is being sent at the room level
      Parameters:
      data - The data of the message being sent.

    • sendMessageToDyad

      <T extends IRoomConnectionData> void sendMessageToDyad(T data, INamedRoomConnection dyad)
      Send a message to a specific dyad-stub in a chatroom. The local machine should wrap this message into a DataPacket and then send it to the specified dyad.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of the message being sent. Bounded by IRoomConnectionData since this is being sent at the room level
      Parameters:
      data - The data of the message being sent.
      dyad - The dyad-stub this message is being sent to.
